The Communist Party of India will take up peopleâ€™s issues and launch agitations across the country in April, according to S. Sudhakar Reddy, national general secretary of the party.Addressing presspersons here on Wednesday, he said district units of the party will meet in February and State units in March and identify the issues to be highlighted.Mr. Reddy alleged that the Union government has failed to control the increasing prices of essential commodities. Rise in prices has hit poor and those who got salary of Rs. 30,000 per month.He claimed that tur dal has cost Rs. 230 a k.g. and onion Rs. 40-Rs. 50 a k.g. Prices of tomatoe reached Rs. 60 a k.g. while the grower got only Rs. 4 a k.g.